<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3587] C# TTLSSocket does not use timeout for opening the socket</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3587</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;TSocket&lt;/tt&gt; class checks for a defined timeout when opening the socket connection and uses a ConnectHelper to perform the &lt;tt&gt;socket.Open()&lt;/tt&gt; call with the defined timeout. The &lt;tt&gt;TTLSSocket&lt;/tt&gt; class does not show this behavior. It simply calls &lt;tt&gt;Open&lt;/tt&gt; without using timeout functionality. The code from &lt;tt&gt;TSocket&lt;/tt&gt; can probably be reused as is in the &lt;tt&gt;TTLSSocket&lt;/tt&gt; class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
